 >> Alice and Bob want to compare salaries without revealing any information
 >> other than equal/not equal. (1) They both interpret their salary as
 >> a phone number. (2) Alice calls the number that corresponds to her salary
 >> and asks for Bob. (3) Bob calls the number that corresponds to his
 >> salary and asks if somebody just called for him.

Including the cents, right?  Otherwise, you'd need a seven figure salary to
make it work! <g>  The other problem is if the number was not in service or
was a modem, FAX machine, or even an answering machine.

Yes, I realize that this was for teaching kids, right?  Otherwise, they
could both just convert their salary to a text string, use a hashing
function on it, then compare the hash values...

